article.headline: (19) SANTA BARBARA 70, ILLINOIS 59
article.story:
SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Lindsay Taylor scored 20 points,
and No. 16 UC Santa Barbara rallied in the second half for a 70-59
victory Friday night over Illinois Friday.

The Gauchos (4-1) extended the nation's second-longest home
winning streak to 27 games. Illinois (1-2) shot 39.6 percent and
was led by Tiffanie Guthrie with 20 points and nine rebounds.

Santa Barbara built an 8-0 lead, but Illinois played solid
defense and took a 32-30 edge by halftime.

In the second half, Illinois expanded its lead to 46-38 at the
15:07 mark when Cindy Dallas buried a pair of free throws.

The Gauchos then went on a 19-4 run over 10 minutes, with Taylor
scoring seven straight points. She nailed a baseline jumper with
1:27 to play to give Santa Barbara its largest lead at 69-55.
